      "author_association" : "CONTRIBUTOR",
      "body" : "[sikulix](https://sikulix-2014.readthedocs.io/en/latest/index.html) is a FOSS tool for automated Graphical testing. It uses Tesseract OCR and OpenCV to verify that the GUI visually looks and works as intended. Using this tool would allow us to write automated graphical tests in python. Additionally we can hook this with [robotframework](https://robotframework.org) and develop some BDD gherkin files which will allow us to test user interaction flows throughout the GUI.",
